translations:
‘The bald boy came, grabbed the (boiling) butter and poured it
			in Kayalo’s mouth, while he was sleeping. He (Kayalo) did not
			move, he stiffened where he sat’ 76/153-154;

I
			pressed it (curd, f.) with my hand, took it out and put it in the
			bag until it dried up’ JL 11.12.9;
